Description: Replay Guitar Exchange presents this Gretsch FSR Electromatic Double Jet - offering a whole new level of style and sound. A chambered double-cutaway basswood body hosts a place for a maple C-shaped neck and rosewood fingerboard to sit, clad in a 1950's reminiscent Seafoam Green colored top with a white back and sides and golden Gretsch hardware (including a trapeze-style G-cutout tailpiece and an Adjusto-matic bridge design). Dual high-sensitive Filter'Tron humbuckers power this Gretsch, with a three-position switch, allowing a variety of tones. This FSR Double Jet is in Near Mint condition, with no issues to speak of, and has an estimated 90% of fret life remaining. An eye-catcher ready to rock out, the Gretsch FSR Electromatic Double Jet is available now at Replay Guitar Exchange!
